{{Infobox sport supporter group | name =Garra Blanca | image = | image_size = 200px | motto = | team = [[Colo-Colo]] | location = [[Santiago]] | established = 1986 | colors = {{color box|#000000}} {{color box|#FFFFFF}} | website = }}
[[Image:Garrablanca.jpg|thumb|300px|View of the ''Garra Blanca'' in the [[Estadio Monumental David Arellano|Estadio Monumental]].]] [[File:Garra Blanca - Salida 03-Oct-09.jpg|thumb|300px|Garra Blanca receiving [[Colo-Colo]] in the [[Estadio Monumental David Arellano|Estadio Monumental]].]]
'''Garra Blanca''' (literally white claw, but in this sense "garra" means force, so the translation is ''white force'') is the title given to a [[Barra brava]] that was created in [[Chile]] by the supporters of [[Santiago, Chile|Santiago]] based [[association football|football]] club [[Colo-Colo]]. It is one of the three largest and most important barras bravas in the country, the other beings [[C.F. Universidad de Chile|Universidad de Chile]]'s ''[[Los de Abajo]]'' (''those from below'') and [[Club Deportivo Universidad Católica|S.C.Universidad Catolica]] "Los Cruzados" ("The Cruzaders").
== History == In early 1986 a youth movement gave rise among the various supporters of Colo-Colo. Amid political repression during the [[military regime]] of [[Augusto Pinochet]], marginalized members of Chilean society decided to unite and form a voice of identity.<ref>{{es icon}} http://garra-blanca.cl/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=43&Itemid=74</ref><ref>{{es icon}} {{cite web |url=http://www.todoalbo.cl/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2008-05-02 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071028101347/http://www.todoalbo.cl/ |archivedate=2007-10-28 |df= }}</ref> Over the years the group has been associated with widescale violence. Fighting with security personnel, the Chilean national police, and other team barra bravas is a common occurrence. Garra Blanca leaders are reported to have an unofficial relationship with Blanco y Negro, the corporate entity that is in charge of Colo-Colo. The board of directors deny such an alliance and have only stated that the barra brava is recognized for stadium safety reasons.<ref>[http://www.emol.com/noticias/deportes/detalle/detallenoticias.asp?idnoticia=276821 Ruiz-Tagle golpeó la mesa: "Blanco y Negro no tiene relación con la barra" | Emol.com<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
