'''Houyele Ba''' (born July 17, 1992) is a [[Mauritania]]n [[middle-distance runner]]. She competed at the [[2016 Summer Olympics]] in the [[Athletics at the 2016 Summer Olympics – Women's 800 metres|women's 800 metres]] race; her time of 2:43.52 in the heats did not qualify her for the semifinals.<ref>{{cite web|title=Houleye Ba |url=https://www.rio2016.com/en/athlete/houleye-ba |website=Rio 2016 |accessdate=September 3, 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160903220724/https://www.rio2016.com/en/athlete/houleye-ba |archivedate=September 3, 2016 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Women's 800m - Standings |url=https://www.rio2016.com/en/athletics-standings-at-womens-800m |website=Rio 2016 |accessdate=September 3, 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160831125140/https://www.rio2016.com/en/athletics-standings-at-womens-800m |archivedate=August 31, 2016 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref>

