{{NBA Development League Awards}}
The '''NBA G League Rookie of the Year''' is an annual [[NBA G League]] (formerly known as the NBA Development League) award given since the league's [[2001–02 NBDL season|inaugural season]] to the top [[rookie]] of the regular season. The league's head coaches determine the award by voting and it is usually presented to the honoree during the playoffs.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dleague.nba.com/news/cantons-quinn-cook-named-2015-16-nba-development-league-rookie-year/|title=Canton’s Quinn Cook Named 2015-16 NBA Development League Rookie Of The Year|work=NBA.com|date=April 11, 2016|accessdate=April 16, 2016}}</ref>

[[Fred House]] was the inaugural winner while playing for the [[Florida Flame|North Charleston Lowgators]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nba.com/dleague/nbdl/rookie_020324.html|title=Lowgators' House Named Rookie of the Year|work=NBA.com|date=March 24, 2002|accessdate=April 16, 2016|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121110215752/http://www.nba.com/dleague/nbdl/rookie_020324.html|archivedate=November 10, 2012|df=}}</ref> Two international players have won the award: [[Edwin Ubiles]] of [[Puerto Rico]] in 2012, and [[Abdel Nader]] of [[Egypt]] in 2017. By [[basketball position|position]], [[guard (basketball)|guards]] have won nine times and [[forward (basketball)|forwards]] eight times. No [[center (basketball)|centers]] have been awarded the Rookie of the Year.

